sql:
SELECT SUM(p.amount) AS total_revenue_generated
FROM payments p
JOIN registrations r ON p.registration_id = r.registration_id;

external_knowledge:
The session statuses are defined as: 
- 'Fully Open' if a session has available spots greater than or equal to the number of registered participants; 
- 'On Waitlist' if the number of registered participants has reached the maximum capacity, but there are still available spots on the waitlist; 
- 'Limited Availability' for all other cases, indicating that the session is not fully open and has no waitlist spots available.

- 'Reached Capacity' implies that the total number of registered participants and waitlisted participants equals the maximum capacity; 
- 'Full Payment' means all registered participants have made their payments; 
- 'Some Payment Pending' means some registered participants have not made their payments yet; 
- 'Partial Payment' means payments have been made, but not all participants have paid in full.

sql:
SELECT SUM(CAST(amount AS REAL)) AS total_revenue
FROM payments
WHERE payment_status = 'paid';

SELECT MAX(num_participants) AS max_registered
FROM (
    SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT r.participant_id) AS num_participants
    FROM registrations r
    GROUP BY r.session_id
) AS session_participants;
